{"body": "This is a utility method, which provides attributes to update bird1 (b1_update), create a new bird (new_b), and destroy bird2 (b2_destroy). I can't name it short enough to avoid horizontal scroliing and make the name more telling than it is at the same time. (Are you familiar with assignments to nested attributes? This method strips the needed content down to the bare minimum.) The combination of changes is necessary to exhibit the second issue - so yes, things are a little complicated. But there is nothing I can do about it.\r\n\r\nMaybe you start by looking at the first set of tests about triggering the callback.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/17284239", "created_at": "2013-05-01T14:34:17Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5476#issuecomment-17284239", "updated_at": "2013-05-01T14:34:17Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5476, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/tandem-softworks", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/34a16f98f4ba99dcb241c8ddb3a5446c?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F1da9a1d31a36bd743246c9900650b600.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks/received_events", "gravatar_id": "34a16f98f4ba99dcb241c8ddb3a5446c", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "tandem-softworks", "type": "User", "id": 1497057, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tandem-softworks/fol